  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: zero tests.** No test files exist anywhere in the repo, and `requirements.txt` doesn't even include `pytest`. This is a from-scratch analysis of 1,505 lines across 8 modules.\n\nRecommended dev dependencies before starting: `pytest`, `pytest-asyncio`, `respx` (or `httpx.MockTransport`) for mocking `httpx`, `freezegun` (or `unittest.mock.patch` on `datetime`) for time-sensitive tests.\n\n---\n\n### `models.py` — highest-value target (pure logic, zero I/O)\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `parse_posted_at`: ms-epoch vs sec-epoch branch, negative epoch, ISO with `Z`, ISO with offset, ISO naive (no tz → should default UTC), garbage string, empty string/None\n- `Job.key` / `content_hash` stability across unrelated field changes (e.g. `posted_at` changing shouldn't change `content_hash`)\n- `Job.to_row()` — confirm `raw` is dropped and `key`/`content_hash` are injected\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expected\", [\n    (\"1643241332430\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),  # ms epoch\n    (\"1643241332\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),      # sec epoch\n    (\"2022-01-26T22:55:32Z\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),\n    (\"2022-01-26T22:55:32+00:00\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),\n    (\"2022-01-26T22:55:32\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),  # naive -> UTC\n    (\"\", None),\n    (\"Posted 3 Days Ago\", None),  # Workday prose - unparseable\n    (\"not-a-date\", None),\n])\ndef test_parse_posted_at(value, expected):\n    assert parse_posted_at(value) == expected\n\ndef test_job_content_hash_ignores_posted_at_and_salary():\n    base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x\", location=\"NYC\")\n    j1 = Job(**base, posted_at=\"2022-01-01\")\n    j2 = Job(**base, posted_at=\"2023-06-01\", salary_range=\"$100k\")\n    assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash\n\ndef test_job_content_hash_changes_on_title():\n    j1 = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n    j2 = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"B\", url=\"u\")\n    assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\ndef test_job_key_format():\n    j = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"123\", title=\"T\", url=\"u\")\n    assert j.key == \"lever:acme:123\"\n\ndef test_to_row_excludes_raw_and_adds_derived_fields():\n    j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", url=\"u\", raw={\"x\": 1})\n    row = j.to_row()\n    assert \"raw\" not in row\n    assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n    assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### `filters.py`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Word-boundary regex matching (substring shouldn't match, e.g. `\"eng\"` shouldn't match `\"engineer\"` unless intended — actually `\\b` allows it since boundary is only on the outer edge; verify `\"cat\"` doesn't match `\"category\"`)\n- exclude takes precedence over include\n- case-insensitivity\n- `locations` substring (not exact) match\n- cutoff: drops old-but-parseable, **keeps** unparseable posted_at (documented behavior — easy regression)\n- `filter_jobs`: `max_age_days` as float/string coercion, missing keys in `rules` dict (defaults)\n\n```python\nimport re\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(title=\"Engineer\", dept=\"\", loc=\"\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\",\n               department=dept, location=loc, posted_at=posted_at)\n\ndef test_match_exclude_wins_over_include():\n    j = _job(title=\"Senior Staff Engineer\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"staff\"]) is False\n\ndef test_match_word_boundary_no_partial_match():\n    j = _job(title=\"Category Manager\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"cat\"]) is False\n\ndef test_match_case_insensitive():\n    j = _job(title=\"ENGINEER\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"]) is True\n\ndef test_match_locations_is_substring_ci():\n    j = _job(loc=\"Remote - New York, NY\")\n    assert match(j, locations=[\"new york\"]) is True\n\ndef test_match_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at():\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday prose, unparseable\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\ndef test_match_cutoff_drops_old_parseable_posting():\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat()\n    j = _job(posted_at=old)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_max_age_days_as_string():\n    jobs = [_job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=100)).isoformat())]\n    assert filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": \"5\"}) == []\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_empty_rules_returns_all():\n    jobs = [_job(), _job(title=\"Other\")]\n    assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### `store.py` — needs an isolated `tmp_path` fixture; no tests exercise SQLite behavior at all\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Fresh DB creates schema (`jobs`, `meta` tables)\n- **Migration path**: opening a pre-existing DB file that lacks `salary_range` column (this is the one genuinely tricky code path — untested entirely)\n- `diff()`: new job inserted; unchanged job (same `content_hash`) only bumps `last_seen`, doesn't go in `changed`; changed job (different hash) goes in `changed` and updates row; mixed batch\n- `get_meta`/`set_meta`: missing key returns `None`; upsert overwrites existing value (`ON CONFLICT`)\n- `added_since`: strict `>` (not `>=`) boundary, ordering by `first_seen, company, title`\n- `count()`\n- context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) closes connection\n\n```python\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", loc=\"\", dept=\"\", url=\"u\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=ext_id, title=title, url=url,\n               location=loc, department=dept)\n\ndef test_schema_created_fresh(store):\n    tables = {r[0] for r in store.conn.execute(\n        \"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table'\")}\n    assert {\"jobs\", \"meta\"} <= tables\n\ndef test_migration_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_db(tmp_path):\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n        CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n            external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n            employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n            first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n    \"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\ndef test_diff_first_seen_is_new(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_job_not_in_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(title=\"T\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"T\")])\n    assert new == [] and changed == []\n\ndef test_diff_content_change_detected(store):\n    store.diff([_job(title=\"Old Title\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"New Title\")])\n    assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\ndef test_diff_updates_last_seen_on_unchanged(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen, last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n    # first_seen must not move even though last_seen does\n    assert row[\"first_seen\"] is not None\n\ndef test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(store):\n    assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n\ndef test_set_meta_upserts(store):\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n    assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\ndef test_added_since_is_strictly_after(store):\n    store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"1\")])\n    ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n    assert store.added_since(ts) == []  # boundary excluded\n\ndef test_count(store):\n    store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"1\"), _job(ext_id=\"2\")])\n    assert store.count() == 2\n```\n\n---\n\n### `pipeline.py`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `load_config`: defaults injected for missing `sources`/`filters`/`db`/`concurrency`; explicit values preserved\n- `run()` dry-run: **does not** touch `Store` at all (currently unverified — a regression here would silently start persisting dedup state during dry runs)\n- `run()` non-dry-run: calls `store.diff`, `dispatch`, returns correct counts\n- `run_sync` delegates to `asyncio.run`\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport pipeline\n\ndef test_load_config_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {} and cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\ndef test_load_config_preserves_explicit_values(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\nconcurrency: 3\\ndb: foo.db\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 3 and cfg[\"db\"] == \"foo.db\"\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_never_touches_store(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[]))\n    with patch(\"pipeline.Store\") as mock_store:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n        mock_store.assert_not_called()\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_persists_and_dispatches(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'j.db'}\\n\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[]))\n    with patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path)\n        mock_dispatch.assert_called_once()\n    assert result[\"matched\"] == 0\n```\n\n---\n\n### `cli.py`\n\n**Gaps:** no test exercises argument parsing or that `--dry-run` actually forwards to `run_sync`.\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport sys\nimport cli\n\ndef test_main_default_config(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"cli.py\"])\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        cli.main()\n        mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=False)\n\ndef test_main_dry_run_flag_forwarded(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(sys, \"argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"--dry-run\", \"-c\", \"other.yaml\"])\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        cli.main()\n        mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"other.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n```\n\n---\n\n### `notify.py`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `notify_console`: new-only, changed-only, both, neither branches\n- `notify_slack`/`notify_webhook`/`notify_email`/`notify_sms`: **early-return guards are untested** (missing env var → no HTTP call at all; empty new+changed → no call even with env set)\n- `notify_email`: SMTP interaction entirely unmocked/untested (`starttls`, conditional `login`)\n- `notify_sms`: `_sms_body` truncation logic (`limit` boundary, `+N more` line), `raise_for_status()` propagating Twilio errors\n- `dispatch()`: **critical gap** — one notifier raising must not prevent others from running (currently only implicitly relied upon, never verified)\n\n```python\nimport os\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\ndef _job(title=\"T\", company=\"C\", salary=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=company, external_id=\"1\", title=title,\n               url=\"https://x\", salary_range=salary)\n\ndef test_notify_console_none(capsys):\n    notify.notify_console([], [])\n    assert \"No fresh listings\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\ndef test_notify_console_new_and_changed(capsys):\n    notify.notify_console([_job(title=\"New\")], [_job(title=\"Changed\")])\n    out = capsys.readouterr().out\n    assert \"NEW listing\" in out and \"UPDATED listing\" in out\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_env(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n        mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_when_empty_even_with_env(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack/x\")\n    with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n        notify.notify_slack([], [])\n        mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\ndef test_notify_slack_posts_payload(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack/x\")\n    with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n        notify.notify_slack([_job(salary=\"$100k\")], [])\n        _, kwargs = mock_post.call_args\n        assert \"$100k\" in kwargs[\"json\"][\"text\"]\n\ndef test_notify_email_noop_without_smtp_host(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SMTP_HOST\", raising=False)\n    with patch(\"smtplib.SMTP\") as mock_smtp:\n        notify.notify_email([_job()], [])\n        mock_smtp.assert_not_called()\n\ndef test_notify_email_logs_in_only_when_user_set(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SMTP_HOST\", \"smtp.x\"); monkeypatch.setenv(\"EMAIL_TO\", \"a@b.com\")\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SMTP_USER\", raising=False)\n    mock_conn = MagicMock()\n    with patch(\"smtplib.SMTP\") as mock_smtp:\n        mock_smtp.return_value.__enter__.return_value = mock_conn\n        notify.notify_email([_job()], [])\n        mock_conn.login.assert_not_called()\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"n_jobs,limit,expect_more_line\", [(5, 8, False), (10, 8, True)])\ndef test_sms_body_truncation(n_jobs, limit, expect_more_line):\n    jobs = [_job(title=f\"J{i}\") for i in range(n_jobs)]\n    body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=limit)\n    assert (\"more\" in body) == expect_more_line\n\ndef test_notify_sms_noop_missing_any_twilio_var(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"x\")\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n    with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n        notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n        mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\ndef test_notify_sms_raises_on_http_error(monkeypatch):\n    for k, v in {\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\": \"sid\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"tok\",\n                 \"TWILIO_FROM\": \"+1\", \"TWILIO_TO\": \"+2\"}.items():\n        monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n    with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n        mock_post.return_value.raise_for_status.side_effect = Exception(\"boom\")\n        with pytest.raises(Exception):\n            notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_notifier_failures(capsys):\n    failing = MagicMock(side_effect=RuntimeError(\"boom\"), __name__=\"failing\")\n    ok = MagicMock(__name__=\"ok\")\n    with patch(\"notify.NOTIFIERS\", [failing, ok]):\n        notify.dispatch([], [])\n    ok.assert_called_once()\n    assert \"failing failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n### `fetchers.py` — largest file, largest gap surface (787 lines, 0 tests)\n\n**A. Retry/backoff core (`_request`) — completely untested, and it's the trickiest logic in the file:**\n\n```python\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nfrom fetchers import _request, _get_json\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_retries_on_429_then_succeeds():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] < 3:\n            return httpx.Response(429)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x\", retries=4)\n    assert r.status_code == 200 and calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_exhausts_retries_raises_runtimeerror():\n    async def handler(request):\n        return httpx.Response(500)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_non_retryable_4xx_raises_immediately():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(404)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x\", retries=4)\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 1  # 404 isn't in the retryable set -> raise_for_status fires once\n```\n\n**B. Parser normalizers — each has untested edge cases:**\n\n| Function | Untested edge cases |\n|---|---|\n| `parse_lever` / `_lever_salary` | missing `salaryRange`, only `salaryDescriptionPlain`, int vs already-string min/max |\n| `parse_ashby` / `_ashby_salary` | `isListed: False` filtered out; missing `id` falls back to `jobId` |\n| `parse_smartrecruiters` | partial location (city only, no region/country) |\n| `parse_recruitee` | location dict vs flat city/country fallback |\n| `parse_workable` | location as dict vs flat fields |\n| `_extract_ds1` / `parse_google` | primary regex fails → fallback regex; both fail → `[]`; malformed embedded JSON → `[]`; short job arrays (defensive indexing) |\n| `_ds1_posted_at` | prefers idx 12 over 13/14; all empty → `\"\"` |\n| `parse_deshaw` | dedup via `seen`; missing location; missing href fallback URL |\n| `parse_twosigma` | 3x-duplicate-card dedup; missing location match |\n| `_amazon_posted_at` | malformed date string → `\"\"` (currently only implicitly covered) |\n| `parse_meta` | duplicate/missing `id` skipped |\n\n```python\nfrom fetchers import (_lever_salary, parse_ashby, _extract_ds1, parse_google,\n                       _ds1_posted_at, parse_deshaw, _amazon_posted_at, parse_meta)\n\ndef test_lever_salary_falls_back_to_description():\n    assert _lever_salary({\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}) == \"Competitive\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_formats_range():\n    assert _lever_salary({\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}) \\\n        == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\ndef test_parse_ashby_filters_unlisted():\n    jobs = parse_ashby(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False}, {\"id\": \"2\"}]})\n    assert [j.external_id for j in jobs] == [\"2\"]\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_fallback_regex_when_sidechannel_missing():\n    html = \"key: 'ds:1', foo, data:[[[\\\"1\\\",\\\"Title\\\"]]]});\"\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == [[\"1\", \"Title\"]]\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty():\n    html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not valid json], sideChannel\"\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\ndef test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_over_update_time():\n    job = [None] * 15\n    job[12] = [1700000000]\n    job[13] = [1800000000]\n    assert \"2023\" in _ds1_posted_at(job)\n\ndef test_parse_deshaw_dedups_repeated_cards():\n    page = ('<div data-job-id=\"1\" class=\"job-display-name\">Eng<'\n            '<div data-job-id=\"1\" class=\"job-display-name\">Eng<')\n    jobs = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expect_empty\", [\n    (\"June 26, 2026\", False),\n    (\"garbage\", True),\n    (\"\", True),\n])\ndef test_amazon_posted_at(value, expect_empty):\n    result = _amazon_posted_at(value)\n    assert (result == \"\") == expect_empty\n\ndef test_parse_meta_skips_duplicate_and_missing_ids():\n    jobs = parse_meta(\"meta\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A dup\"},\n                                {\"title\": \"no id\"}])\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n```\n\n**C. Paginated fetchers — no test drives the pagination stop conditions, which is where real bugs hide:**\n\n```python\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_workday, fetch_google, fetch_amazon\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_workday_stops_when_offset_reaches_total():\n    def handler(request):\n        body = request.read()\n        offset = int(__import__(\"json\").loads(body)[\"offset\"])\n        if offset >= 20:\n            return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobPostings\": [], \"total\": 20})\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\n            \"jobPostings\": [{\"title\": f\"J{offset}\", \"externalPath\": \"/p\",\n                              \"bulletFields\": [str(offset)]}],\n            \"total\": 20})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_workday(client, {\"host\": \"h\", \"tenant\": \"t\", \"site\": \"s\",\n                                             \"page_size\": 20})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_workday_safety_cap_at_5000_offset():\n    # total never reported correctly -> must stop via the offset > 5000 safety cap,\n    # not loop forever\n    ...\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_google_stops_on_first_empty_page():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] == 1:\n            return httpx.Response(200, text=\"key: 'ds:1', data:[[['1','T']]], sideChannel\")\n        return httpx.Response(200, text=\"key: 'ds:1', data:[[]], sideChannel\")\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        jobs = await fetch_google(client, {\"company\": \"google\", \"max_pages\": 5})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1 and calls[\"n\"] == 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_amazon_dedups_across_pages():\n    # server returns overlapping ids on page boundary -> `seen` set must prevent dupes\n    ...\n```\n\n**D. `fetch_source` / `fetch_all` — orchestration untested:**\n\n```python\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_valueerror():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_per_source_failures(capsys):\n    async def ok(client, source): return [object()]\n    async def boom(client, source): raise RuntimeError(\"network down\")\n    with patch.dict(\"fetchers.FETCHERS\", {\"ok\": ok, \"boom\": boom}):\n        jobs = await fetch_all([{\"ats\": \"ok\", \"company\": \"a\"},\n                                 {\"ats\": \"boom\", \"company\": \"b\"}])\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n    assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_closes_only_owned_client():\n    external_client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n    await fetch_all([], client=external_client)\n    assert not external_client.is_closed\n    await external_client.aclose()\n```\n\n---\n\n### `agent.py`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first run (no marker) uses `since_days` window; truncation only at `first_seen` group boundaries (the trickiest logic in this file — a naive slice would split a batch mid-timestamp-group); `watermark` output correctness\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now`, valid watermark, invalid ISO watermark → exit code 2 + stderr, neither arg → exit code 2\n- `_normalize_ats`: replacements skip `<style>`/`<script>` blocks and tag attributes, only touch text nodes; counts dict accuracy\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env override, `PATH` lookup via `shutil.which`, macOS app bundle fallback, none found → `sys.exit`\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file → exit 2; Chrome invocation produces non-PDF output → exit 1 with stderr tail printed; temp file cleanup (`tmp.unlink`) even on exception\n- `main()`: mode-word vs flag-passthrough split logic (`words[:i]` / `words[i:]`), `-i`/`--interactive` stripped from mode words but forces interactive\n\n```python\nimport sys\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport agent\nfrom store import Store\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_now(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n    assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 0\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"j.db\") as s:\n        assert s.get_meta(\"last_scan\") is not None\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_invalid_watermark_exits_2(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n    assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n    assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_no_args_exits_2(tmp_path):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n    assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\ndef test_db_new_truncates_only_at_group_boundary(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    db = tmp_path / \"j.db\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db}\\n\")\n    from models import Job\n    with Store(db) as s:\n        # two jobs sharing one first_seen timestamp (one pipeline run)\n        s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\"),\n                Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"2\", title=\"B\", url=\"u\")])\n    agent.cmd_db_new([\"--limit\", \"1\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])  # limit smaller than the group\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 0 or out[\"count\"] == 2  # never 1 - group not split\n    assert out[\"truncated\"] is True\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_style_and_script_blocks():\n    html = \"<style>content: '\\u2014';</style><p>em\\u2014dash</p><script>'\\u2014'</script>\"\n    fixed, counts = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n    assert \"\\u2014\" in fixed  # inside <style>/<script>, untouched\n    assert \"em-dash\" in fixed  # inside <p> text, replaced\n    assert counts.get(\"em-dash\") == 1\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_tag_attributes():\n    html = '<a title=\"caf\\u00e9\\u2014note\">text\\u2014here</a>'\n    fixed, counts = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n    assert 'title=\"caf\\u00e9\\u2014note\"' in fixed  # attribute untouched\n    assert \"text-here\" in fixed\n\ndef test_chrome_bin_prefers_env_var(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    fake = tmp_path / \"chrome\"\n    fake.write_text(\"\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", str(fake))\n    assert agent._chrome_bin() == str(fake)\n\ndef test_chrome_bin_exits_when_nothing_found(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", raising=False)\n    with patch(\"shutil.which\", return_value=None), \\\n         patch(\"pathlib.Path.exists\", return_value=False):\n        with pytest.raises(SystemExit):\n            agent._chrome_bin()\n\ndef test_cmd_pdf_render_missing_input_exits_2(tmp_path, capsys):\n    rc = agent.cmd_pdf_render([str(tmp_path / \"nope.html\")])\n    assert rc == 2\n\ndef test_main_splits_mode_words_at_first_flag():\n    with patch(\"agent.run_claude\") as mock_run:\n        agent.main.__wrapped__ if False else None\n    # verify argv [\"scan\", \"extra\", \"--foo\"] -> mode_words=[\"scan\",\"extra\"], extra=[\"--foo\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n### Integration test gaps (none exist today)\n\n1. **Full pipeline round-trip**: mock `fetch_all` to return fixed `Job` list → run `pipeline.run()` twice against a real `tmp_path` SQLite DB → assert first run reports all as `new`, second run reports 0 new/0 changed (true dedup behavior, not unit-mocked).\n2. **CLI → pipeline → store**: invoke `cli.main()` via `subprocess` with a temp `sources.yaml` pointing at a `greenhouse` source, using `respx`/`MockTransport` to fake the network, and assert the resulting `jobs.db` has rows.\n3. **`agent.py db-new` / `db-mark` scan-cycle integration**: run a pipeline import, then `db-new` (verify JSON output matches inserted rows), then `db-mark <watermark>`, then `db-new` again (verify it returns 0 new since the marker advanced) — this is the core loop `modes/scan.md` depends on and has zero coverage.\n4. **`notify.dispatch` with all notifiers \"enabled\"** via env vars and a shared `httpx.MockTransport`, asserting Slack/webhook/SMS each receive one call and a raised exception in one doesn't block the rest (currently only testable in isolation per-function above; needs one test that wires all five together).\n5. **Fetcher registry cross-check**: assert every ATS name in `sources.yaml` config resolves via `FETCHERS` (a config/code drift check that would catch a typo in `sources.yaml` before a live run).\n\n---\n\n### Priority order (given zero existing coverage)\n1. `models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py` — pure/deterministic logic, cheapest to test, highest bug-catching value (dedup and content-hash correctness underlie everything).\n2. `fetchers.py` parsers (`parse_*`) — no network needed, defends against ATS payload-shape regressions.\n3. `notify.py` guard clauses and `dispatch` isolation — cheap, prevents \"notifier crash kills entire run\" regressions.\n4. `fetchers.py` pagination/retry logic and `agent.py` — need `httpx.MockTransport`/subprocess mocking, more setup but cover the trickiest control flow in the repo.\n5. Integration tests last, once units are solid.\n",
