        "title": "Integration test gaps (none exist today)",
        "content": "\n1. **Full pipeline round-trip**: mock `fetch_all` to return fixed `Job` list → run `pipeline.run()` twice against a real `tmp_path` SQLite DB → assert first run reports all as `new`, second run reports 0 new/0 changed (true dedup behavior, not unit-mocked).\n2. **CLI → pipeline → store**: invoke `cli.main()` via `subprocess` with a temp `sources.yaml` pointing at a `greenhouse` source, using `respx`/`MockTransport` to fake the network, and assert the resulting `jobs.db` has rows.\n3. **`agent.py db-new` / `db-mark` scan-cycle integration**: run a pipeline import, then `db-new` (verify JSON output matches inserted rows), then `db-mark <watermark>`, then `db-new` again (verify it returns 0 new since the marker advanced) — this is the core loop `modes/scan.md` depends on and has zero coverage.\n4. **`notify.dispatch` with all notifiers \"enabled\"** via env vars and a shared `httpx.MockTransport`, asserting Slack/webhook/SMS each receive one call and a raised exception in one doesn't block the rest (currently only testable in isolation per-function above; needs one test that wires all five together).\n5. **Fetcher registry cross-check**: assert every ATS name in `sources.yaml` config resolves via `FETCHERS` (a config/code drift check that would catch a typo in `sources.yaml` before a live run).\n\n---\n\n",
